Former French First Lady Valerie Trierweiler has revealed she is contemplating writing a tell-all book about her relationship with President Francois Hollande.

The 48-year-old made the comments during a two-day-long humanitarian trip to India earlier this week after the French President ended their relationship.

Speaking to Parisien Magazine, in an interview to be published on Friday, she said: 'I do not rule out writing a book.'

